ROY CAMPANELLA HOSPITALIZED IN SERIOUS CONDITION 
Roy Campanella, the Dodgers' former Hall of Fame catcher and a member of the 
club's community services department since 1978, is in serious condition at 
Northridge Hospital with pneumonia and diabetes complications, a hospital 
spokeswoman said Friday. 
Campanella, 68, was admitted to the hospital Dec. 30 and has been on a 
respiratory machine to assist his breathing. 
A Dodger spokesman who spoke with Campanella's wife, Roxie, Friday said she 
reported that Campanella was doing well and had shown improvement in the last 
24 hours. 
